result.execSummary:
The defendant Nancy Ann Villegas was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct - Loud and Boisterous Conduct in a Private Place [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Bond previously posted in the amount of $150 has been applied. Remaining costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed. The defendant must make herself available to have a DNA sample collected at the Waushara County Sheriff's Department in the event that she would return to the State of Wisconsin provided that a sample had not previously been provided.

Case called @ 2:04 p.m. Defendant Nancy Ann Villegas in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DA Blader - Defendant has complied with the terms of the agreement, recommending costs. Defendant waives right to counsel and waives right to be personally present in the courtroom. The Court accepts the defendant's voluntary waiver of counsel and will allow the defendant to appear telephonically. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. DA Blader makes statement on behalf of the victim. No statement by the defendant. Court orders: Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA sample and surcharge - DE must make herself available to have a DNA sample provided should she return to the State of Wisconsin. Defendant may inquire about having the sample taken at another jail in her current location should they be willing to take the sample and forward to our Sheriff's Department. Bond previously posted to be applied.  Appeal rights mailed to the defendant.

Case Called @ 1:58 PM: Defendant Nancy Ann Villegas in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def wants counsel - states she cannot afford a retainer on her own.  Def did speak with SPD on eligibility.   She is a seasonal employee with her assignment ending on 10/2/2015 and she will leave the area.  Off Record for Def to speak with the State on resolution.  Back of Record @ 2:10 PM:  Per ADA resolution reached and recited.  State will amend Ct 1 to DC that is loud and boisterous with Domestic and weapon enhancer dismissed.  12 mos Deferred SEH agreement and terms recited.  No contact provision with completion of Anger Mgmt.  If successful completion, Court Costs will be requested.  Defendant advised of right to counsel.  Court accepts voluntary waiver of counsel.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained.  Consequences explained for failure to abide by terms of Deferred SEH Agreement. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Court accepts State's Motion to allege boisterous DC in private place.  Plea:  GP  Dismsses Weapon Enhancer attached to Complaint.  Court accepts plea and stays JOC.  Court accepts terms and conditions of Deferred SEH Agreement.  Sentencing Stayed for 1 yr.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 12, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
